class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534161\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534161\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ymx1665702675781.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ymx1665702675781.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ymx1665702675781.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ymx1665702675781\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Print Queue\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span> specifies the destination of the printed output.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__p_d9686e1_d9687e1_d9688e1\">You can use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span> to create a print file, spawn an operating system command, or print the output and delete the print file.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Valid Print Queue Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n Entry\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n No value\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Writes the output to a Uniface print file in the current working directory (unless redirected through the assignment file).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">PRINTMAN</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Sends the output to the Microsoft Windows Print Manager, which displays the Print dialog box that allows you to specify printer properties.\n <p class=\"p\">If you do not want this dialog box to appear, specify <code class=\"ph codeph\">/NODIALOG</code> in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">PORT</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">Sends the output directly to the logical printer\n                     specified in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span> field, for example,\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">LPT1:</code>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n @<var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Spawns an operating system <var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var>, passing the printed output to <var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var> as a parameter.\n <p class=\"p\">(The <code class=\"ph codeph\">@</code> can be omitted on Microsoft Windows.)</p>\n<p class=\"p\">More parameters can be added in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span> field.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n #<var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Spawns the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var>synchronously, passing the printed output to <var class=\"keyword varname\">Command</var> as a parameter.\n <p class=\"p\">Uniface waits for the command to complete before continuing.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__1\">\n Other value\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymx1665702675781__table_d1022e1_d1023e1_d1024e1__entry__2\">\n Generates the print command for the operating system, appending any <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span> specified. The generated command depends on the operating system, version, and Uniface version. For example, on Unix it would be:\n <p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">lp -s -d</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintQueue</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintFileName</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintOptions</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__section_pgy_hdl_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838631e219\">Spawning Commands </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__p_d9692e1_d9693e1_d9694e1\">If the first character is the <code class=\"ph codeph\">@</code> symbol,\n            Uniface spawns the subsequent text as a command to the operating system and passes the\n            name of the print file as a parameter, followed by any <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print\n               Options</span>. This feature enables you to write your own printing procedures\n            and shell scripts.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__section_j4p_3dl_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838631e234\">Command Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__p_d9698e1_d9699e1_d9700e1\">The constituent parts of the command that Uniface spawns\n            can be accessed in a script using the following parameters:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__ul_ncq_kdl_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__li_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$0</code>—value of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print\n                  Queue</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__li_d4466e1_d4467e1_d4468e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$1</code>—<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintFileName</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__li_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$2</code> through\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$n</code>—options given in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__section_efz_kdl_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838631e273\">Example: Windows: Executing Commands in a Windows Command Window</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__p_d9704e1_d9705e1_d9706e1\">In this example, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span>\n            starts a command window and the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Options</span> specifies further\n            instructions to redirect the standard input (coming from Uniface) to a file\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">myfile.ps</span>.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__fig_d9707e1_d9708e1_d9709e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__fig_ucq_mdl_5cc\">\n<img alt=\"Graphical content\" class=\"image\" id=\"ymx1665702675781__image_vcq_mdl_5cc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/printjobmodel_userdefined.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guw1665702607063.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Job Models</a><p>A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bsm1665702989373.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Files</a><p>A print file is created by Uniface using the specified print job model and print mode.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xhc1665702675851.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Options</a><p>Print options provide additional parameters for the operating system print command, or the command specified in Print Queue.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534161\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534161\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Print Queue Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Print Queue The Print Queue specifies the destination of the printed output. You can use the Print Queue to create a print file, spawn an operating system command, or print the output and delete the print file. Table 1. Valid Print Queue Values Entry Meaning No value Writes the output to a Uniface print file in the current working directory (unless redirected through the assignment file). PRINTMAN Sends the output to the Microsoft Windows Print Manager, which displays the Print dialog box that allows you to specify printer properties. If you do not want this dialog box to appear, specify /NODIALOG in Print Options . PORT Sends the output directly to the logical printer specified in the Print Options field, for example, LPT1: . @ Command Spawns an operating system Command , passing the printed output to Command as a parameter. (The @ can be omitted on Microsoft Windows.) More parameters can be added in the Print Options field. # Command Spawns the Command synchronously, passing the printed output to Command as a parameter. Uniface waits for the command to complete before continuing. Other value Generates the print command for the operating system, appending any Print Options specified. The generated command depends on the operating system, version, and Uniface version. For example, on Unix it would be: lp -s -d PrintQueue PrintFileName PrintOptions Spawning Commands If the first character is the @ symbol, Uniface spawns the subsequent text as a command to the operating system and passes the name of the print file as a parameter, followed by any Print Options . This feature enables you to write your own printing procedures and shell scripts. Command Parameters The constituent parts of the command that Uniface spawns can be accessed in a script using the following parameters: $0 —value of Print Queue $1 — PrintFileName $2 through $n —options given in Print Options Example: Windows: Executing Commands in a Windows Command Window In this example, the Print Queue starts a command window and the Print Options specifies further instructions to redirect the standard input (coming from Uniface) to a file myfile.ps . Related Links Print Job Models A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print. Print Files A print file is created by Uniface using the specified print job model and print mode. Print Options Print options provide additional parameters for the operating system print command, or the command specified in Print Queue. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}